SIMPLE: earwig
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Earwig
<hw>Ear"wig`</hw> <pr>(⟦emac⟧r"w⟦icr⟧g`)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[AS.
<ets>e⟦aacute⟧rwicga</ets>; <ets>e⟦aacute⟧re</ets> ear +
<ets>wicga</ets> beetle, worm: cf. Prov. E.
<ets>erri-wiggle</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <fld>(Zo⟦oum⟧l.)</fld>
<def>Any insect of the genus <gen>Forficula</gen> and related genera,
belonging to the order <ord>Dermaptera</ord> (formerly
<ord>Euplexoptera</ord>). They have elongated bodies and a prominent
pair of curved pincers at the rear of their abdomen.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source> + <source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Zo⟦oum⟧l.)</fld> <def>In America, any small
chilopodous myriapod, esp. of the genus <gen>Geophilus</gen>. See
<er>Geophilus</er></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><note>⟦hand⟧ Both insects are so called from the supposition that
they creep into the human ear.</note>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>A whisperer of insinuations; a secret
counselor.</def> <rj><au>Johnson.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Earwig</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Earwig
<hw>Ear"wig`</hw> <pr>(⟦emac⟧r"w⟦icr⟧g`)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos>
<vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p. p.</pos> <conjf>Earwigged</conjf>
<pr>(⟦emac⟧r"w⟦icr⟧gd`)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Earwigging</conjf> <pr>(⟦emac⟧r"w⟦icr⟧g*g⟦icr⟧ng)</pr>.]</vmorph>
<def>To influence, or attempt to influence, by whispered insinuations or
private talk.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧No longer was he <xex>earwigged</xex> by the
Lord Cravens.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Lord Campbell.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Earwitness</ent>⟦br⟧
